Sentencas: Composites of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) with Sr-doped LaFeO3 (LSF) were studied for application as high-performance cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Fabrication of Sr-doped LaFeO3YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: The composites were formed by aqueous impregnation of porous YSZ with La, Sr, and Fe salts, followed by calcination at various temperatures.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sr-doped LaFeO3YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction measurements showed that the LSF perovskite phase had formed by 1023 K and that solid-state reaction with the YSZ did not occur below approximately 1223 K.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sr-doped LaFeO3YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: The electronic conductivity of the 40 wt % LSF-YSZ composite was maximized by calcination at 1123 K. SOFCs prepared with a 40 wt % LSF-YSZ cathode showed improved performance over SOFCs prepared with conventional LSM-YSZ cathodes at 973 K, although the performance of cells made with cathodes having lower LSF content did not perform as well.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sr-doped LaFeO3YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: Based on measurements with a reference electrode on an electrolyte-supported cell, the impedance of the 40 wt % LSF-YSZ cathode is approximately 0.1 ohm cm(2) in air at 973 K. Finally, a cathode-supported cell was fabricated from a 40 wt % LSF-YSZ cathode and shown to perform well in H-2.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sr-doped LaFeO3YSZ composite cathodes
